#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: actors-cluster-isdown
description: Actor v1.23 — broadcastHealth + clusterIsDown single-node behaviour
---

# Cluster-wide failure detector — single-node

In single-node mode there are no peers, no phi vectors arrive, and so
`clusterIsDown(nodeId)` returns `false` for any candidate (no data ⇒
not enough votes for "down").  `broadcastHealth()` is a no-op when
there are no peers but must not crash.

Multi-node aggregation (majority vote across delivered phi vectors)
is exercised by the integration suite; this conformance test pins the
no-data branch across all three backends.

```scalascript
runActors {
  broadcastHealth()  // no-op
  println("down=" + clusterIsDown("never-connected"))
  println("ok")
}
```
